]]'' || Mary Andrews || \"The Road to Edinburgh\" || [[Rod Amateau]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1958 || ''[[General Electric Theater]]'' || Ruth Marshall || \"Strange Witness\" || [[Herschel Daugherty]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1959 || ''The Joan Crawford Show''<ref>TV pilot for ''The Joan Crawford Show'' unsold series</ref> || Susan Conrad || \"Woman on the Run\" || [[Dick Powell]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1959 || ''[[General Electric Theater]]'' || Ann Howard || \"And One Was Loyal\" || [[Herschel Daugherty]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1959 || ''[[The Joseph Cotten Show]]'' || Ruth Marshall || \"Strange Witness\" || [[Herschel Daugherty]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1959 || ''[[Dick Powell's Zane Grey Theatre|Zane Grey Theatre]]'' || Stella Faring || \"Rebel Range\" || [[Don Medford]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1961 || ''[[Dick Powell's Zane Grey Theatre|Zane Grey Theatre]]'' || Sarah and Melanie Hobbes || \"One Must Die\" || [[Lewis Allen (director)|Lewis Allen]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1961 || ''[[The DuPont Show of the Week]]'' || Hostess || \"The Ziegfeld Touch\" || James Elson || [[NBC]]\n|-\n| 1963 || ''[[Route 66 (TV series)|Route 66]]'' || Morgan Matheson Harper || \"[[List of Route 66 episodes|Same Picture, Different Frame]]\" || [[Philip Leacock]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1967 || ''[[The Man from U.N.C.L.E.]]'' || Amanda True || \"[[List of The Man from U.N.C.L.E. episodes|The Five Daughters Affair: Part 1]]\"<ref>Different scenes were shot and turned into the theatrically released feature film ''The Karate Killers''.</ref> || [[Barry Shear]] || [[NBC]] \n|-\n| 1968 || ''[[The Lucy Show]]'' || Herself (guest star) || \"[[List of The Lucy Show episodes|Lucy and the Lost Star]]\" || [[Jack Donohue (director)|Jack Donohue]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1968 || ''[[The Secret Storm]]'' || Joan Borman Kane #2<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">Temporary replacement for Christina Crawford</ref> || [daytime soap opera] || [[Gloria Monty]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1969 || ''[[Greta Garbo|Garbo]]'' || Hostess / Narrator || [made-for-TV documentary] || [[